Simple example TBX application to show how to create a document based application.

Running the application puts an icon on the iconbar.

The iconbar menu gives two options.
- show the application information
- quit the application

Clicking select on the iconbar shows a blank document window.

Dragging a file to the icon bar or double clicking on a file to type 0x010 will open the window with the contents of the file.

The window consists of a display field that shows a single line of text in a writable field.

Editing this line updates the underlying document. The menu from this window allows you to see the documents file information and save it.

